$\begin{align}
\dfrac{4^8}{4^3}&=4^{8-3}
\\\\
&=4^5
\end{align}$

This follows from the general rule $\dfrac{x^m}{x^n}=x^{m-n}$. Note that the powers have the same base.

We can also see this is correct by expanding the powers.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{4^8}{4^3}&=\dfrac{\overbrace{\cancel 4\cdot \cancel 4\cdot \cancel 4\cdot 4\cdot 4\cdot 4\cdot 4\cdot 4}^\text{8 times}}{\underbrace{\cancel 4\cdot \cancel 4\cdot \cancel 4}_\text{3 times}}
\\\\\\
&=\underbrace{4\cdot 4\cdot 4\cdot 4\cdot 4}_\text{5 times}
\\\\
&=4^5
\end{align}$

